# Component Rules

## Structure
- Functional components only. No class components.
- Keep components under ~200 lines. Extract a sub-component rather than growing.
- One component per file. Named export matching the filename.
- Sub-components used only within one file can live in the same file, below the main export.

## Props
- Always type props with an inline `interface Props { ... }` at the top of the file.
- Use `useCallback` for functions passed as props to child components.
- Never pass the whole AppState down — pass only the slice the component needs.

## Tailwind
- Utility classes directly on elements. No custom CSS files.
- No inline `style={{}}` except for genuinely dynamic values (e.g. computed widths).
- Use `no-print` class on anything that must not appear in the print stylesheet.
- Don't write 15-class strings on one element — extract a sub-component.
- Responsive: lg: prefix for desktop-only layout (sidebar, wide table).

## Forms
- Never use `<form>` elements — use div + onClick handlers.
- All number inputs: `type="number"`, `min={0}`, `step={0.25}` for hour fields.
- All selects: controlled via value + onChange.
- Labels: always associate with `htmlFor` / `id`.

## Print behaviour
- The print stylesheet hides `.no-print` elements globally (defined in index.html).
- Sticky table columns are reset to static on print — account for this in layout.
- ScheduleView switches content based on `activeTab`; only the visible section prints.

## Shared components available (import from @/components/shared/)
Tooltip | TimeEstimateInput | SelectField | RadioGroup | CertaintyBadge
StepNav (from @/components/calibration/StepWizard)
